metadata.name: Aurora
metadata.description:
In a world where deformities abound,
Where beauty's meaning has been forgotten,
Amidst agendas and misguided ideas,
Replacement of our kind with uncivilized souls.

But know, true beauty still persists,
Unaffected by mundane agendas,
It shines brighter than the sun,
Eternal and unwithering.

Your art, O great artist,
Brings beauty to the hearts of people,
Inspiring dreams and uplifting spirits,
May it ignite a light in the darkness.

So do not despair, continue to create,
For beauty must thrive in this world,
And let reason return to humanity,
Reviving true beauty once again.
